INSERT INTO `su_kien` VALUES (1,'Ionah - A must see show in Hanoi','Star Galaxy','87 L&amp;#225;ng Hạ, Ba Đ&amp;#236;nh, H&amp;#224; Nội , Quận Ba Đ&amp;#236;nh, H&amp;#224; Nội','                                                                  Welcome to Ionah,    A fascinating journey filled with colors, you will experience a story magical yet realistic, with your favourite Hanoi flavour combine with Western beauty.    The name &ldquo;Ionah&rdquo; would sound like a foreign name from a distant land, but it is in fact truly familiar. &ldquo;Ionah&rdquo; is &ldquo;Hanoi&rdquo; written in reverse, a gift originated from the love for Hanoi.    Ionah is the one and only art entertainment program in Vietnam with perfect combination between circus art, choreography, acting and many more, supported by world class theatrical technology. After 2 years with over 300 performances, Ionah has become an essential experience for both Vietnamese and foreign audiences alike.    Ch&agrave;o mừng bạn đến&nbsp;với Ionah,   Một chuyến đi th&uacute; vị v&agrave; đầy m&agrave;u sắc sẽ mang kh&aacute;n giả&nbsp;tới với c&acirc;u chuyện vừa thực vừa ảo, vừa mang dấu ấn H&agrave; Nội vừa giao thoa với n&eacute;t đẹp T&acirc;y Phương.    Nghe c&aacute;i t&ecirc;n &ldquo;Ionah&rdquo; tưởng như một c&aacute;i t&ecirc;n lạ lẫm xứ &Acirc;u Ch&acirc;u n&agrave;o đ&oacute;, nhưng thực ra lại v&ocirc; c&ugrave;ng giản dị v&agrave; rất H&agrave; Nội. &ldquo;Ionah&rdquo; ch&iacute;nh l&agrave; viết ngược của H&agrave; Nội, l&agrave; t&igrave;nh cảm, t&acirc;m huyết của ekip s&aacute;ng tạo d&agrave;nh tặng ri&ecirc;ng cho H&agrave; Nội.    Ionah l&agrave; chương tr&igrave;nh giải tr&iacute; đầu ti&ecirc;n v&agrave; duy nhất tại Việt Nam c&oacute; sự kết hợp h&agrave;i h&ograve;a giữa c&aacute;c loại h&igrave;nh nghệ thuật như xiếc, vũ đạo, diễn xuất... c&ugrave;ng c&ocirc;ng nghệ 3D v&agrave; &acirc;m thanh hiện đại. Sau gần 2 năm kể từ khi ra mắt, trải qua hơn 300 suất diễn, Ionah&nbsp;đ&atilde; trở th&agrave;nh một m&oacute;n ăn tinh thần kh&ocirc;ng thể n&agrave;o thiếu đối với cả người Việt lẫn du kh&aacute;ch quốc tế.    Even with duration of only 75 minutes, Ionah never fail to wow the audience. You will not only meet with the classic scenery of Hanoi&rsquo;s Long Bien Bridge or the Old Quarters, but also the surreal images of a world that is Ionah.   Chương tr&igrave;nh chỉ d&agrave;i 75 ph&uacute;t, nhưng cũng đủ khiến cả kh&aacute;n ph&ograve;ng phải đi từ bất ngờ n&agrave;y tới bất ngờ kh&aacute;c. Bởi họ kh&ocirc;ng chỉ bắt gặp đ&acirc;u đ&oacute; những h&igrave;nh ảnh ch&acirc;n thật v&agrave; gần gũi của H&agrave; Nội với cầu Long Bi&ecirc;n, 36 phố phường m&agrave; c&ograve;n l&agrave; những khung cảnh huyền ảo trong thế giới si&ecirc;u thực của ri&ecirc;ng Ionah.      &nbsp;      Delivering a messege of love and life, a blend of the classic and the modern, Ionah has created a trend and offers a new look into Vietnamese art culture. The show tells it&rsquo;s audience about a Hanoi that is rich in history, yet integrated and developed.    Truyền tải th&ocirc;ng điệp về t&igrave;nh y&ecirc;u v&agrave; sự sống, với sự h&ograve;a quyện giữa những nền văn h&oacute;a kh&aacute;c biệt, giữa truyền thống v&agrave; hiện đại, Ionah đ&atilde; tạo ra xu hướng v&agrave; thổi một l&agrave;n gi&oacute; mới v&agrave;o l&agrave;ng nghệ thuật giải tr&iacute; Việt Nam. Mang đến cho c&aacute;c du kh&aacute;ch quốc tế một c&aacute;i nh&igrave;n mới về H&agrave; Nội, một H&agrave; Nội kh&ocirc;ng chỉ c&oacute; bề d&agrave;y văn h&oacute;a nghệ thuật m&agrave; c&ograve;n l&agrave; một th&agrave;nh phố hội nhập v&agrave; ph&aacute;t triển.        The elements of Ionah     	Combine circus art with many other unique art forms   	World-class theatrical technology   	Combination of both modern and folk music   	Alluring and unique costumes   	Suitable for all ages   	Mostly non-verbal, eliminating all language boundaries between the show and it&rsquo;s audiences​       Ionah is where all the most passionate and top-tier artists gather, always eager to perform their best to create the greatest performances.    Ionah&rsquo;s creative team consists of experts in the art culture of Vietnam:     	Creator &amp; Director: Phạm Ho&agrave;ng Nam   	Music Director:&nbsp; Quốc Trung   	Choreographer: Trần Ly Ly   	Circus Director: Meritorious Artist Tống To&agrave;n Thắng   	Image Creator: Fernando Toma   	Costume Designer: Nguyễn C&ocirc;ng Tr&iacute;     &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; Đặc trưng Ionah   	Kết duy&ecirc;n xiếc với c&aacute;c loại h&igrave;nh nghệ thuật độc đ&aacute;o   	Hiệu ứng s&acirc;n khấu v&agrave; c&ocirc;ng nghệ 3D hiện đại   	&Acirc;m nhạc điện tử kết hợp chất liệu &acirc;m nhạc d&acirc;n gian   	Trang phục độc đ&aacute;o v&agrave; ph&ugrave; hợp với từng nh&acirc;n vật   	Ph&ugrave; hợp với tất cả mọi đối tượng, lứa tuổi.   	Chương tr&igrave;nh kh&ocirc;ng sử dụng lời n&oacute;i n&ecirc;n ng&ocirc;n ngữ kh&ocirc;ng l&agrave; trở ngại đối với người xem.     Ionah l&agrave; nơi quy tụ những nghệ sỹ xiếc v&agrave; m&uacute;a đầy đam m&ecirc; v&agrave; l&ograve;ng y&ecirc;u nghề. Họ l&agrave; những nghệ sỹ trẻ, t&agrave;i năng, v&ocirc; c&ugrave;ng nhiệt huyết, lu&ocirc;n lu&ocirc;n sẵn s&agrave;ng cống hiến cho kh&aacute;n giả những m&agrave;n tr&igrave;nh diễn tuyệt vời nhất.​    &Ecirc; k&iacute;p s&aacute;ng tạo của Ionah bao gồm những gương mặt gạo cội h&agrave;ng đầu của l&agrave;ng giải tr&iacute; Việt:     	Kịch bản &amp; Tổng đạo diễn/ Creator &amp; Director: Phạm Ho&agrave;ng Nam   	Gi&aacute;m đốc &acirc;m nhạc/ Music Director:&nbsp; Quốc Trung   	D&agrave;n dựng &amp; Bi&ecirc;n đạo/ Choreographer: Trần Ly Ly   	Đạo diễn xiếc/ Circus Director: NSƯT Tống To&agrave;n Thắng   	Gi&aacute;m đốc h&igrave;nh ảnh/ Image Creator: Fernando Toma   	Thiết kế trang phục/ Costume Designer: Nguyễn C&ocirc;ng Tr&iacute;)                                                                                              '),(2,'L&amp;#224;ng T&amp;#244;i - Nh&amp;#224; H&amp;#225;t Tuồng Việt Nam','Nh&amp;#224; H&amp;#225;t Tuồng Việt Nam','51A Đường Th&amp;#224;nh, Quận Ho&amp;#224;n Kiếm, Th&amp;#224;nh Phố H&amp;#224; Nội','                                                                  	GIỚI THIỆU L&Agrave;NG T&Ocirc;I       	L&agrave; sản phẩm s&aacute;ng tạo đầu ti&ecirc;n của nh&oacute;m t&aacute;c giả Tuấn L&ecirc; - Nguyễn L&acirc;n &ndash; Nhất L&yacute; &ndash; Tấn Lộc, cũng l&agrave; nh&oacute;m t&aacute;c giả của &Agrave; Ố Show. L&agrave;ng T&ocirc;i đ&atilde; biểu diễn hơn 300 suất tại nhiều nước tr&ecirc;n thế giới từ 2009 đến 2012: H&agrave; Lan, Ph&aacute;p, Bỉ, Đức, T&acirc;y Ban Nha, Hy Lạp, Thụy Sĩ, Hong Kong.       	&nbsp;    	L&agrave;ng T&ocirc;i l&agrave; một bức tranh l&agrave;ng qu&ecirc; Bắc Bộ b&igrave;nh y&ecirc;n, khi ng&agrave;y mới bắt đầu với tiếng g&agrave; g&aacute;y s&aacute;ng, những đứa trẻ chơi đũa tre trong l&uacute;c cha mẹ l&agrave;m việc ngo&agrave;i đồng ruộng. Nơi những người n&ocirc;ng d&acirc;n h&uacute;t thuốc l&agrave;o với chiếc điếu c&agrave;y bằng tre, l&uacute;c nghỉ giải lao dưới b&oacute;ng c&acirc;y giữa nắng trưa h&egrave; gay gắt. Nơi tối đến, những cặp t&igrave;nh nh&acirc;n t&igrave;nh tự tr&ecirc;n những c&acirc;y cầu tre dưới &aacute;nh s&aacute;ng của h&agrave;ng ng&agrave;n v&igrave; sao.       	Với kỹ thuật xiếc mới, tre ch&iacute;nh l&agrave; linh hồn của vở diễn, l&agrave; người dẫn dắt c&acirc;u chuyện, x&acirc;y dựng v&agrave; thay đổi c&aacute;c khung cảnh, kết nối hai mươi nghệ sĩ xiếc v&agrave; nhạc c&ocirc;ng H&agrave; Nội trong sắc m&agrave;u &acirc;m thanh của c&aacute;c nhạc cụ truyền thống.       	&nbsp;    	&nbsp;    	MY VILLAGE VERSION AT A GLANCE       	&nbsp;    	My Village is a delicate merge of tradition and innovation, where poetic beauty of Northern Vietnam&rsquo;s village life is presented under new cirque approach.       	Farming, building activities, traditional games, lifestyle of Northern villagers are recreated by ancestral bamboo props, breath-taking cirque and rhythmic dance, juggling, and acrobatic movements to distinct folk music played from more than 20 musical instruments.       	&nbsp;    	The show was created in 2005 in Hanoi, by the same creators of &Agrave; Ố Show. My Village toured around the world from 2009 to 2012, with over 300 shows in France, Holland, Spain, Belgium, Greece, Switzerland, Germany, Hong Kong.       	&nbsp;    	\r\n  	A&nbsp;BLEND&nbsp;OF\r\n  	Bamboo&nbsp;Cirque\r\n  	Acrobatics\r\n  	Contemporary&nbsp;Dance\r\n  	Choreography       	\r\n  	MUSIC\r\n  	Live\r\n  	17&nbsp;Vietnamese&nbsp;musical&nbsp;instruments.       	\r\n  	DURATION\r\n  	Approximately&nbsp;60&nbsp;minutes       	&nbsp;    	** All the seats are on a &quot;best available&quot; basis. If you made online payment ,we will contact you to arrange the seats. If you choose COD, we will choose the best available seats for you.&nbsp;If you buy two or more tickets, we&#039;ll make sure that you all sit together.       	&nbsp;    	  		E-ticket holder must arrive 45 minutes before show time in order to exchange e-ticket for Theater Pass.     	  		Theater doors will be closed 15 minutes before show time.         	&nbsp;    	NẾU QU&Yacute; KH&Aacute;CH MUỐN ĐẶT NHIỀU V&Eacute; HƠN SO VỚI SỐ LƯỢNG C&Oacute; SẴN TR&Ecirc;N HỆ THỐNG, HOẶC ĐẶT SAU 9H30 S&Aacute;NG NG&Agrave;Y C&Oacute; SUẤT DIỄN, XIN VUI L&Ograve;NG LI&Ecirc;N HỆ HOTLINE CỦA TICKETBOX.       	&nbsp;    	PLEASE CONTACT US IF YOU NEED MORE TICKETS OR BOOK TICKETS AFTER 09:30AM (ON SHOW DAY).       	--------------------------------------------------------------      	&nbsp;    	                                                                                            '),(3,'Vở diễn Tứ Phủ - The Four Palaces show','Rạp C&amp;#244;ng Nh&amp;#226;n','42 Tr&amp;#224;ng Tiền, Quận Ho&amp;#224;n Kiếm, Th&amp;#224;nh Phố H&amp;#224; Nội','                                                                &nbsp;  A UNIQUE TRADITIONAL PERFORMANCE     MỘT VỞ DIỄN ĐỘC Đ&Aacute;O BẠN KH&Ocirc;NG THỂ BỎ QUA     &nbsp;     &nbsp;  The Four Palaces show&nbsp;is an innovative production of director Viet Tu, inspired by the ritual &quot;Deity reincarnation&quot; in Vietnamese Mother Goddess&nbsp;worship. The show attracted audience thanks to light, sound and cultural and spiritual content. Director Viet Tu said he spent three years to learn and took another one year to set up ideas. What he wants to do is to recreate the original &quot;deity reincarnation&quot;&nbsp;ceremony to introduce to international friends on their visit to Hanoi. The show&nbsp;is going to take&nbsp;place 12 times a month. The performance lasts&nbsp;45 minutes, consisting of three parts corresponding to three sessions: &quot;Chau De Nhi&quot;, &quot;Mr. Hoang Muoi&quot; and &quot;Co&nbsp;Be&nbsp;Thuong Ngan&quot;.   (Vở diễn&nbsp;Tứ Phủ&nbsp;l&agrave; sản phẩm s&aacute;ng tạo&nbsp;đạo diễn Việt T&uacute;, được lấy cảm hứng từ nghi lễ &quot;Hầu đồng&quot; trong t&iacute;n ngưỡng thờ Mẫu của Việt Nam. Chương tr&igrave;nh thu h&uacute;t kh&aacute;n giả nhờ yếu tố &aacute;nh s&aacute;ng, &acirc;m thanh v&agrave; nội dung đậm văn h&oacute;a, t&acirc;m linh. Đạo diễn&nbsp;Việt T&uacute; cho biết anh d&agrave;nh ba năm để t&igrave;m hiểu v&agrave; mất th&ecirc;m một năm l&ecirc;n &yacute; tưởng d&agrave;n dựng. Những g&igrave; anh muốn l&agrave; t&aacute;i hiện nghi lễ&nbsp;&quot;Hầu đồng&quot;&nbsp;gốc của người Việt để giới thiệu c&ugrave;ng bạn b&egrave; quốc tế mỗi lần gh&eacute; thăm H&agrave; Nội. Chương tr&igrave;nh diễn ra 12 suất trong một th&aacute;ng.&nbsp;Vở diễn k&eacute;o d&agrave;i 45 ph&uacute;t, gồm ba phần tương ứng với ba gi&aacute; hầu: &quot;Chầu Đệ Nhị&quot;, &quot;&Ocirc;ng Ho&agrave;ng Mười&quot; v&agrave; &quot;C&ocirc; B&eacute; Thượng Ng&agrave;n&quot;).    &nbsp;  Actors of the Four Palaces&nbsp;take the role of&nbsp;the &quot;Thanh dong&quot; and &quot;Hau dang&quot;, which are both extremely important and indispensable in the reincarnation&nbsp;ritual. In the play, costumes&nbsp;of the art of reincarnation&nbsp;are honored by the&nbsp;details and meticulousness when two &quot;Hau dang&quot; help &quot;Thanh dong&quot;&nbsp;change clothes. In addition, audience will be&nbsp;immersed in the space of tradiational&nbsp;art&nbsp;when the Chau Liter (Vietnamese typical music of Mother Goddess worship) is harmonized with traditional folk musical instruments:&nbsp;drums, lute, zither&nbsp;and flute.   (C&aacute;c diễn vi&ecirc;n của Tứ Phủ h&oacute;a th&acirc;n th&agrave;nh Thanh đồng v&agrave; Hầu d&acirc;ng vốn l&agrave; hai nh&acirc;n tố cực k&igrave; quan trọng v&agrave; kh&ocirc;ng thể thiếu được trong nghi lễ Hầu đồng. Trong vở diễn, những bộ khăn chầu, &aacute;o ngự của nghệ thuật Hầu đồng được t&ocirc;n vinh bằng sự chi tiết v&agrave; tỉ mỉ khi hai Hầu d&acirc;ng trợ gi&uacute;p Thanh đồng thay đổi trang phục. B&ecirc;n cạnh đ&oacute;, kh&aacute;n giả sẽ thực sự ch&igrave;m đắm v&agrave;o kh&ocirc;ng gian nghệ thuật d&acirc;n tộc khi những điệu Chầu văn (loại h&igrave;nh lễ nhạc đặc trưng của t&iacute;n ngưỡng thờ Mẫu của người Việt) được h&ograve;a c&ugrave;ng giai điệu với c&aacute;c nhạc cụ d&acirc;n gian: trống, đ&agrave;n nguyệt, đ&agrave;n tranh v&agrave; s&aacute;o.)    &nbsp;  The show&nbsp;has received many ambassadors, cultural attaches from France, Italy, Poland, Hungary, Canada or UNICEF to attend and receive&nbsp;a lot of praise.   (Chương tr&igrave;nh từng đ&oacute;n tiếp nhiều đại sứ, t&ugrave;y vi&ecirc;n văn ho&aacute; của Ph&aacute;p, Italy, Ba Lan, Hungary, Canada hay UNICEF đến dự v&agrave; nhận được rất nhiều lời khen ngợi.)    &nbsp;     C&aacute;c Thanh Đồng trong buổi lễ thay trang phục nhiều lần với sự trợ gi&uacute;p của cộng sự để h&oacute;a th&agrave;nh th&aacute;nh thần. Đi k&egrave;m phần biểu diễn l&agrave; c&aacute;c giai điệu chầu văn. Loại h&igrave;nh lễ nhạc n&agrave;y sử dụng nhạc cụ truyền thống như đ&agrave;n nguyệt, s&aacute;o, ph&aacute;ch, đ&agrave;n bầu... C&aacute;c l&agrave;n điệu ch&iacute;nh bao gồm: Bỉ, Miễu, Thổng, Ph&uacute; B&igrave;nh, Ph&uacute; Ch&ecirc;nh, Ph&uacute; N&oacute;i, Đưa Thơ, V&atilde;n, Dọc...   &nbsp;  (The &quot;Thanh dong&quot;&nbsp;in the ceremony changed costumes with the help of associates to transform into&nbsp;Goddess. Accompanying the performance is the chanting melody. This type of ritual&nbsp;uses traditional instruments such as  moonstone, flute, zither&nbsp;and beat. The main tunes include: Bi, Mieu, Thong, Phu Binh, Phu Chenh, Phu&nbsp;Noi, Do&nbsp;Tho, Van, Doc, etc.)    &nbsp;     &nbsp;     &nbsp;  MORE PHOTOS FROM THE SHOW     MỘT SỐ H&Igrave;NH ẢNH KH&Aacute;C TẠI BUỔI DIỄN     &nbsp;     &nbsp;     &nbsp;     &nbsp;     &nbsp;     &nbsp;     &nbsp;  SEAT MAP    SƠ ĐỒ CHỖ NGỒI    &nbsp;     &nbsp;  &nbsp;  &nbsp;  &nbsp;                                                                                           '),(4,'BitCoin Thực chiến - 3 Chiến lược gi&amp;#250;p bạn kiếm BTC trong 2018','UP Coworking Space','Tầng 8, t&amp;#242;a nh&amp;#224; Hanoi Creative City, 1 Lương Y&amp;#234;n, Bạch Đằng, Hai B&amp;#224; Trưng, H&amp;#224; Nội 100000, Quận Hai B&amp;#224; Trưng, Th&amp;#224;nh Phố H&amp;#224; Nội','                                                                Offline BitClub H&agrave; nội   Tr&acirc;n trọng k&iacute;nh mời c&aacute;c anh chị v&agrave; c&aacute;c bạn tham dự sự kiện offline ph&acirc;n t&iacute;ch cơ hội kinh doanh&nbsp;&quot;BitCoin Thực chiến - 3 Chiến lược gi&uacute;p bạn kiếm BTC trong 2018&quot;. Đ&acirc;y l&agrave;&nbsp;chương tr&igrave;nh đặc biệt v&agrave; duy nhất đầu năm 2018&nbsp;m&agrave; BitClubHN&nbsp;tổ chức để giới thiệu loại h&igrave;nh kinh doanh tạo ra nguồn thu nhập thụ động trong thị trường BitCoin.  Mục đ&iacute;ch của chương tr&igrave;nh gi&uacute;p bạn hiểu rất r&otilde; 3 chiến lược kiếm tiền, điểm mạnh v&agrave; yếu của từng loại trong THỰC CHIẾN, hiểu&nbsp;s&acirc;u v&agrave; r&otilde; về cơ chế của hoạt động&nbsp;đầu tư trong đ&agrave;o BitCoin.  Về cuối chương tr&igrave;nh, gi&aacute; trị bạn nhận được sẽ l&agrave; kiến thức v&agrave; những cơ hội đầu tư khiến đồng tiền&nbsp;của m&igrave;nh hoạt động hiệu quả cũng như c&oacute; thể trực tiếp tham gia v&agrave;o hoạt động đ&agrave;o đồng BitCoin cũng như c&aacute;c đồng tiền số kh&aacute;c ngay lập tức.  Ai n&ecirc;n tham dự?  Nếu bạn c&oacute; bất kỳ c&acirc;u hỏi n&agrave;o dưới đ&acirc;y:  - Chưa c&oacute; V&iacute; BITCOIN v&agrave; cần c&oacute; th&ocirc;ng tin để nhanh ch&oacute;ng tham gia v&agrave;o thị trường Blockchain.  - Chiến thuật Buy and Hold tại sao kh&ocirc;ng hiệu quả?  - Giao dịch (Trading) c&ograve;n thua lỗ, tại sao? c&oacute; n&ecirc;n trading?  - Hoạt động &quot;đ&agrave;o&quot; tiền điện tử c&oacute; thực sự sinh l&atilde;i?  - Cơ chế &quot;đ&agrave;o&quot; l&agrave; như thế n&agrave;o?  - L&agrave;m thế n&agrave;o kiểm so&aacute;t chi ph&iacute; &quot;đ&agrave;o&quot; v&agrave; kiểm tra tốc độ &quot;đ&agrave;o&quot; của một đối t&aacute;c khi đ&atilde; ủy th&aacute;c cho họ?  - Đặc biệt: C&aacute;ch ứng dụng cơ chế &quot;H&ograve;n tuyết lăn&quot;, hay &quot;L&atilde;i suất k&eacute;p&quot; để đạt tự do t&agrave;i ch&iacute;nh bền vững trong thị trường Crypto.  Sẽ kh&ocirc;ng vấn đề g&igrave; nếu bạn l&agrave; người mới bắt đầu hay kh&ocirc;ng am hiểu về c&ocirc;ng nghệ. Bởi v&igrave;, trong hội thảo n&agrave;y, bạn kh&ocirc;ng những được chia sẻ chi tiết, m&agrave; ch&uacute;ng t&ocirc;i c&ograve;n c&oacute; phần giao lưu đặt c&acirc;u hỏi mở để đảm bảo c&aacute;c bạn hiểu r&otilde; về k&ecirc;nh đầu tư mang lại thu nhập thụ&nbsp;động n&agrave;y.  Chi tiết của chương tr&igrave;nh như sau:&nbsp;  Diễn giả &Ocirc;ng Huy&ecirc;n&nbsp;Vũ&nbsp;  - T&aacute;c giả cuốn s&aacute;ch đ&atilde; xuất bản tr&ecirc;n 5 ch&acirc;u lục bằng tiếng Anh, tiếng Nhật v&agrave; tiếng Nga &quot;BitCoin thực chiến - 3 Chiến lược gi&uacute;p ch&uacute;ng t&ocirc;i kiểm được 400 BTC trong năm 2017&quot; S&aacute;ch hiện c&oacute; gi&aacute;&nbsp;23.35$ tr&ecirc;n amazon, đ&atilde; b&aacute;n 500+ bản, dịch 3 thứ tiếng Anh, Nhật, Nga v&agrave; đ&aacute;nh gi&aacute; 4.3 sao  - Founder của BitClubHN&nbsp;  Thời gian:&nbsp;09:00 đến 12:00 ng&agrave;y Chủ nhật 25/03/2018  Địa điểm:&nbsp;UP Coworking Space -&nbsp;Tầng 8, t&ograve;a nh&agrave; Hanoi Creative City, 1 Lương Y&ecirc;n, Bạch Đằng, Hai B&agrave; Trưng, H&agrave; Nội&nbsp;  Nội dung:  09:00 - 09:30 Đ&oacute;n tiếp\r\n 09:30 - 09:40 3 chiến lược đầu tư BitCoin - ph&acirc;n t&iacute;ch\r\n 09:40 - 10:30 Giới thiệu BitClubNetwork&nbsp;\r\n 10:30 - 11:00 BitClubNetwork &amp; QA\r\n 11:00 - 11:15 Đăng k&yacute; - nhận qu&agrave; tặng\r\n 11:15 - 11:30 QA  Lệ ph&iacute; tham dự  V&eacute; sớm:&nbsp; 119.000 VNĐ / 2 người.  V&eacute; thường: 500.000 VNĐ / người - k&egrave;m ưu đ&atilde;i;  V&eacute; VIP : 2.200.000 VNĐ / người, chụp ảnh c&ugrave;ng c&aacute;c diễn giả, ghế ngồi gần s&acirc;n khấu - k&egrave;m ưu đ&atilde;i;  Ưu đ&atilde;i đặc biệt:  1. Tất cả th&agrave;nh vi&ecirc;n c&oacute;&nbsp;v&eacute; đều được hỗ trợ:   	Gi&uacute;p khởi tạo&nbsp;v&iacute; BTC đầu ti&ecirc;n (nếu chưa c&oacute;)   2. Th&agrave;nh vi&ecirc;n mua v&eacute; thường sẽ được nhận qu&agrave; tặng l&agrave;:   	Bản dịch tiếng việt của cuốn s&aacute;ch &quot;BitCoin thực chiến - 3 Chiến lược gi&uacute;p ch&uacute;ng t&ocirc;i kiểm được 400 BTC trong năm 2017&quot; hiện c&oacute; gi&aacute;&nbsp;23.35$ tr&ecirc;n amazon, đ&atilde; b&aacute;n 500+ bản, dịch 3 thứ tiếng Anh, Nhật, Nga v&agrave; đ&aacute;nh gi&aacute; 4.3 sao (số lượng c&oacute; hạn)   3. Th&agrave;nh vi&ecirc;n mua v&eacute; VIP sẽ được nhận qu&agrave; tặng l&agrave;:   	T&agrave;i khoản BCN thực chiến trị gi&aacute; 99$ 	Tặng&nbsp;BitCoin trải nghiệm lu&ocirc;n nếu chưa c&oacute; v&iacute; BitCoin 	Bản dịch tiếng việt của cuốn s&aacute;ch &quot;BitCoin thực chiến - 3 Chiến lược gi&uacute;p ch&uacute;ng t&ocirc;i kiểm được 400 BTC trong năm 2017&quot; hiện c&oacute; gi&aacute;&nbsp;23.35$ tr&ecirc;n amazon, đ&atilde; b&aacute;n 500+ bản, dịch 3 thứ tiếng Anh, Nhật, Nga v&agrave; đ&aacute;nh gi&aacute; 4.3 sao   Tr&acirc;n trọng,  BitClubHN  &nbsp;  p.s nếu số lượng tham gia kh&ocirc;ng đủ, ch&uacute;ng t&ocirc;i c&oacute; thể chuyển v&eacute; của qu&yacute; vị sang th&aacute;ng tiếp theo;                                                                                           '),(5,'TEDxHanoi 2018 Toward a Global Community','UNIS Hanoi Campus','G9 Ciputra Hanoi, Quận T&amp;#226;y Hồ, Th&amp;#224;nh Phố H&amp;#224; Nội','                                                                You&rsquo;re invited to get inspired at the latest TEDx event in Hanoi, taking place on 2nd June at the United Nations International School (UNIS) Hanoi in Ciputra.   TEDxHanoi 2018 is a day-long experience for people who care about ideas, connections and curiosity. Join us and hear from some of the most intriguing speakers from Hanoi and beyond as they explore this event&rsquo;s theme &ldquo;Toward to a Global Community&rdquo;: Connect. Enable. Inspire.   The world is becoming a smaller place. It&rsquo;s easier now than ever before to move commerce around the globe; to study on foreign soil; and most of all to share ideas. This year&rsquo;s TEDxHanoi conference will explore the theme of humanity living as one globalized community.   Our world has become inextricably linked together. So how do we ensure the best for our local community in this larger web? How do we ensure the best for this global community as a whole?   Throughout June 2nd, our lineup of expert speakers will share their visions for their local communities, and for the wider one that we are all a part of. From their unique backgrounds in business, education, research, tech and the arts, their perspectives will each offer a piece of the puzzle to the riddle of how we manage and participate in a community of such scale.   -----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------  Buying tickets  There are two types of tickets: Early bird and Standard.  100 Early bird tickets available to buy online from April 2nd: 880,000 VND (Sold out)  250 Standard tickets available to buy online and offline from April&nbsp;13th until&nbsp;May 26th: 1,080,000 VND  A ticket includes:  A full-day stage&nbsp;program&nbsp;with 12-14 live speakers with expertise in the fields of business, education, research, tech and the arts. (The speaker list will be announced on May 1st).  Complementary lunch buffet of healthy food.  TEDxHanoi gift bag&nbsp;including sweets, treats and vouchers from the TEDxHanoi organizers and our partners.&nbsp;  Interactive workshops and entertainment&nbsp;throughout the day including music, dance and yoga.&nbsp;  Hanoi&rsquo;s finest and brightest&nbsp;all together in one room &ndash; an unparalleled networking opportunity.  Buying more than 10 tickets? Contact us at tedxhanoi2018@gmail.com for group discount (10% off).  When you buy tickets directly from our website, you are required to provide your available email address in order to receive an e-ticket. The e-ticket might be sent to your promotion tab, please move Ticketbox email to your Primary tab and save&nbsp;it.&nbsp;  Leading to the event we will send you more information about the speakers, the program, dress code and so forth .&nbsp;  Please bear&nbsp;in mind that we do not encourage you to buy ticket from any individuals or organizations&nbsp;except Ticketbox.&nbsp;  If you encounter any difficulties in ticket purchase, please do not hesitate to contact us at hotline: 0968 246 155  -----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------  SPEAKER LINE UP  Madam Ton-Nu-Thi Ninh  President, Ho Chi Minh City Peace and Development Foundation\r\n Vice President, Viet Nam Peace Committee\r\n Former Ambassador of Viet Nam to the E.U and Belgium (2000 &ndash; 2002)\r\n Former Vice-chair, Foreign Affairs Committee, Viet Nam National Assembly\r\n (2002 &ndash; 2007)  Following ten years in academe in Paris and Saigon/Ho Chi Minh City, Madam Ninh served as a career diplomat specializing in global issues (international peace and security, development, environment, governance and human rights) and multilateral institutions before being elected to Viet Nam&rsquo;s National Assembly where she continued to actively work to build bridges of understanding and cooperation between Viet Nam and the world, more particularly highlighting the National Assembly&rsquo;s integral role in Viet Nam&rsquo;s &ldquo;Doi Moi&rdquo; (Reform and Renewal) and democratization.  Today, she consistently pursues her lifelong commitment to Viet Nam&rsquo;s sustainable development and more effective integration with the world. Through her frequent interaction with the public, especially youth, women and the media, she is known as one of the public figures with a meaningful voice in Viet Nam.  Madam Ninh has been awarded the French Legion d&rsquo;Honneur (Commandeur), the Belgian Order of Leopold II, and the Vietnamese Medal of Labor &ndash; First Class. The Royal Melbourne Institute of Technology (RMIT) has conferred upon her an Honorary Doctorate of Social Science.  Ann Morgan  Writer  Ann Morgan is a UK-based writer, editor and Royal Literary Fund fellow. Following the success of her project to read a book from every country in 2012, which led to a TED talk and the non-fiction book Reading the World, Ann continues to blog about international literature at ayearofreadingtheworld.com. Her debut novel, Beside Myself, has been translated into nine languages.  Giang Le  Artist  Born 1988 in Hanoi, Vietnam. Le Giang pursued her B.A in Art Education at Vietnam University of Fine Art and M.A in Studio Practice at Camberwell College, University of the Arts London, UK. Le Giang explores the hypothesis that there could be a future with no humanity, with only barren structures and ruined remnants of human being. She practices with different mediums such as installations, sculptures to drawings and painting with the subjects range from found artifacts to ruin architectures. Le Giang is also an art educator. In 2013, she founded Blossom Art House - an art center focusing on educating arts to local community. In 2015, Le Giang co-founded Six Space, an artist run initiative endeavours to provide diversity in approaches and perspectives to art and creative practices in Hanoi.  Huong Le  Environmental activist  L&ecirc; Nguyễn Thi&ecirc;n Hương is an educator by day and an environmental activist by night. She has been working in the field of education for a decade at different roles - a tutor, a teaching assistant, a teacher, a counselor, an admissions officer, etc. On the other hand, traveling has always been a big part of her life. And her expedition to Sơn Đo&ograve;ng in 2014 has marked a big turning point for her. At the time, Hương was in the process of applying to graduate school for the major of Educational Psychology. But what she found out at Sơn Đo&ograve;ng has changed her direction completely. Her #SaveSonDoong campaign earned her a scholarship to Brandeis University, where she did two Master degrees in Nonprofit Management and Sustainable Development.  Jieun Baek  Debater  Jieun (Judy) Baek is a junior at United Nations International School. She is a part of Vietnam Youth Leaders, a service group at UNIS Hanoi established under the aim of becoming a local hub of communication in the Vietnamese Hanoi society. She is also a member of the Vietnamese debate national team for World Schools Debate Championships, one of the most prestigious competitions in the debate society. She started debate when she was in grade 2, and has been in and out of the activity ever since. In her free time, she translates sponsor letters from sponsored children to their sponsors. She has taught English to students as a student mentor at the schools she has been to, since grade 6.  Laura Sheehan  Career Strategist  Laura E.P. Sheehan - Career Strategist and Founder of E.P. Career Strategies Laura is a U.S. lawyer turned expat career strategist who stumbled upon her life&rsquo;s calling whilst living in Hanoi. Having decided years ago to accompany her husband in his international career moves, Laura has lived in seven countries over the span of 15 years. Mere weeks into her time in Hanoi, Laura seized upon a new opportunity to utilize her experiences to empower the wider global community of &ldquo;trailing spouses.&rdquo; In the two short years that she has been in Vietnam, she has successfully made a full transition into the role of a global career strategist. Laura was recently recognized by the Associates of the American Foreign Service Worldwide (AAFSW) as a top nominee for the 2017 &ldquo;Champion of Career Enhancement for Eligible Family Members (CCE-EFM)&rdquo; Award and was featured in the AAFSW&rsquo;s January 2018 edition of Global Link.  Minh Giang  PhD in Food Science and Nutrition  Dr. Giang Thuy Minh (Minh Giang) holds a Ph.D. in Food Science and Nutrition from AgroParisTech, Paris, France. Her main research interests include human nutrition, healthy food including their digestion and absorption, food anthropology, food education and formation. After finishing her Ph.D. thesis on lipid digestion and absorption, she is now a lecturer at the Department of Food Technology and Nutrition of Hoa Sen University. Currently, she is working on a research about antioxidant determining and characterizing in Vietnamese vegetables. Besides her academic career, she is also very active in publicly promoting good lipid consumption by writing news on social media. She is also running a non-government organization in education called Vietnam Journal of Science, created and contributed by a team of young Vietnamese experts from various disciplines. This serves as an online science magazine that popularizes science news and knowledge for everybody, especially young people.  Quan Do  Poetry translator  Minh Quan Do is a junior at UNIS Hanoi. He is an aspiring poet and poetry translator. He first started when he was in 8th grade, and has continued to do so since. He&#039;s currently working on a a portfolio with his poetry, both translated and original, as well as a project titled &ldquo;Lost In Translation&rdquo;, which seeks to identify the effect of poetry on meaning. He&#039;s currently working with two startups, both related to food and beverage, in which he takes marketing advisory roles. He is also a leader at the Vietnam Youth Leaders group, which is a networking group that he and three friends started this year to create a localized version of networks like Entrepreneurs Organization (EO), and a member of the student-led charity, SANSE.  Rashmi Sharma  Leadership Consultant  Rashmi&rsquo;s favorite word is antifragile &ndash; the skill of gaining from disorder, which she believes is key for thriving global communities. In her quest to be antifragile, her chance encounter with jazz dance led her to dancing across eight international locations while unlearning profound leadership lessons which inspired this talk. Currently she leads Learning and Wellbeing for South East Asia &amp; Australasia for Unilever. Prior to that she was with IBM and Aon where she led &amp; consulted with diverse leaders on unlocking people potential. She has been recipient of several coveted titles such as Top 25 HR professionals in India and one of the top 10 women in the Economic Times Young Leaders List. Rashmi enjoys being an idea catalyst and has been a thought leader at industry forums, most notably UN Youth Speak 2017 by AIESEC along with ministry of education. She has also co-authored transformation case study for Richard Ivey School of Business.  Tan Hui Woon  Founder &amp; Managing Partner, Alley 51 Ventures  In a span of 12 years, Hui Woon has worn several hats as Strategist Marketeer, Business Consultant, Entrepreneur and Investor. Her first venture in Vietnam 7 years back began as a consulting firm, where she worked closely with startup CEOs and Founders ranging from F&amp;B, FMCG, real estate and retail to tap into new market and business opportunties. Hence when founding Mash and The Purpose Group in 2013, she dedicated herself with a bold vision: changing the game of brand-building through unconventional yet purposeful solutions and campaigns. Most recently she founded Alley 51 Ventures, an up-and-coming Venture Builder that aims to rapidly build startups that aren&rsquo;t only profitable but exists to solve hard problems in SEA and emerging markets. At Alley 51 Ventures, Hui Woon focuses on empowering young entrepreneurs and strengthening the Vietnam startup ecosystem. Hui Woon graduated with honors from University of Technology, Malaysia with a Bachelor in Chemical Engineering.  Tien Luong  Educator  Luong Trung Tien is the co-founder of Tay May To Mo, an educational YouTube channel. For years, Tay May To Mo has been providing quality science program for VIetnamese community. Through enjoyable videos, Tay May To Mo promoted the curiosity and the love for knowledge among young learners and educators. With the will to make possitive impact to Vietnamese education, Luong Trung Tien decided to become teacher at AmericanSTEM, an organization that provides STEM education for K-12 students in Vietnam.  Trang Nguyen  Wildlife conservationist  Trang Nguyen is a wildlife conservationist and research scientist. She is also a founder and director of a Vietnamese NGO called WildAct. Currently she is working closely with the polices and anti-poaching units in Africa, as well as authorities in Asia to map out the illegal wildlife trade between these two continents. In 2014, she was immortalized as an online game character to raise awareness about the African rhino crisis and drew more than 2 millions players to the plight of rhino conservation within the first two weeks of the game launch. In 2018, Trang was awarded as one of the three winners of Future for Nature Award - a well-respected award for wildlife conservationists across the globe. She was also awarded as one of the 30 young influential people under 30 years old by Forbes Vietnam. She published her book &quot;Back to the wilderness&quot; about her works on the wildlife crime in Asia and Africa.  Trung Mai  Architect  Trung is a Paris based architect, urban designer. He earned his bachelor and master in architecture with honors from ENSA Paris-Malaquais before becoming a French licensed architect at Ecole sp&eacute;ciale d&#039;architecture, Paris. Trung also completed a civil engineering degree at Paul Sabatier University of ToulouseIII. Trung has been a recipient of the Erasmus scholarship for exchange programs at Leibniz University of Hanover, Germany and Architectural Association, UK. Trung has worked in different international offices and projects, in France, Iran, Senegal, Japan and Vietnam. Currently working for the international urban planning department of AREP Group, Paris, the largest architecture firm in France. In parallel, he has founded atelier MAI as an experimental design practice and urban research platform He has won VEX 2018, Spec Go Green International award 2017, Unbuilt Vision 2015, U.S, ASA International design competition 2015.  --------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------  View our TEDx event at https://tedxhanoi.org/    Or on TED.com at https://www.ted.com/tedx/events/27996   Contact us at tedxhanoi2018@gmail.com  &nbsp;                                                                                           '),(6,'[Hanoi] MAU5TRAP PRESENTS: DEADMAU5','THE TOILET','6th Floor, 41 Hai Ba Trung, Quận Ho&amp;#224;n Kiếm, Th&amp;#224;nh Phố H&amp;#224; Nội','   